Gauteng's Human Settlements Department say it has a plan to relocate and rehouse Mamelodi flood victims. The department's spokesperson Tahir Sema speaks to #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng's Human Settlements Department says it has a plan to rehouse Mamelodi flood victims. But these plans will apply only to those who live in areas identified as a risk to life. Last year, hundreds of families were affected by floods in the province. The department's Tahir Sema has cautioned people against occupying vacant land, saying it's punishable by law. Watch the video above for more details.